radiographic_examinations.findings: The liver is normal in echogenicity throughout. There are no focal hepatic masses. There is no intrahepatic biliary dilatation. The common bile duct is normal measuring up to 4 mm. The main portal vein is patent with appropriate direction of flow. The gallbladder demonstrates a few tiny shadowing gallstones. The right kidney measures 12.2 cm. The left kidney measures 13.3 cm. Both kidneys are normal in appearance without hydronephrosis, stones, or mass. The spleen and visualized aspects of the pancreas are within normal limits. Limited view of the intrauterine pregnancy demonstrates an appropriate fetal heart beat.
